# Example Ollama Modelfile.
#
# Unsloth's save_pretrained_gguf() already writes a ready-to-use Modelfile inside
# the export directory (./spidey-brain/Modelfile) with the correct chat template.
# Use THAT one first. This hand-written version is here only if you want to set the
# system prompt or stop tokens yourself.
#
# 1) Check the actual .gguf filename in your export dir (name varies by base model/quant):
#      ls spidey-brain/*.gguf
# 2) Point FROM at it, then: ollama create spidey-brain -f ./Modelfile.example

FROM ./spidey-brain/unsloth.Q4_K_M.gguf

PARAMETER temperature 0.1
# Qwen models end turns with <|im_end|>. For Llama-3.x use <|eot_id|> instead.
PARAMETER stop "<|im_end|>"

SYSTEM """You are Spidey, an autonomous coding assistant. Complete tasks by calling the
provided tools. Inspect files before you edit them, verify changes by running commands,
and call the finish tool with a short summary when the task is done."""
